{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review laws on parental support & financial responsibility during pregnancy",
        "additional_details": "Pregnancy can be a vulnerable time, and many mothers experience a lack of support that goes beyond financial absence. Financial responsibility for a child typically begins after birth and we feel there is limited recognition of a parent\u2019s conduct during pregnancy. Decisions around birth registration may often be made when mothers are vulnerable.\r\n \r\nWe believe the law should be reviewed to consider whether a parent\u2019s absence, lack of support, or abandonment during pregnancy should be formally recognised and taken into account by courts where relevant.",
        "background": "Launch a review into UK family law to examine financial responsibility for a child during pregnancy and to consider whether courts should formally recognise a lack of emotional, physical, and practical support from a parent during pregnancy as a relevant factor in decision-making.",
